{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/openclawguide"]}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"role":"collectionGroup","title":"Running OpenClaw in Virtual Machines","roleHeading":"API Collection"},"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Run two isolated OpenClaw AI agent instances on a single Mac — each with its own workspace, channels, and API keys."}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Related","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/ProvisioningMode","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineSpecification","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SharedFolder","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/OpenClawTemplate"],"anchor":"Related"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Guides","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarted","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CLIReference","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GitHubActionsGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning"],"anchor":"Guides"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/openclaw.ai"},{"type":"text","text":" is an open-source self-hosted AI assistant"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that connects to Claude, GPT-4, Gemini, and other models. Running OpenClaw"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in macOS VMs with Spooktacular gives you:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Isolation"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — each instance has its own macOS environment, API keys,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and workspace. A misconfigured agent can’t affect the other."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"2 instances per Mac","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — Apple Silicon’s 2-VM kernel limit maps","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"perfectly to running a pair of agents (e.g., work + personal,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or production + staging)."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Snapshots"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — save a working OpenClaw configuration, experiment,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and roll back if something breaks."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Kubernetes-managed"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" — scale OpenClaw instances across a fleet"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of Macs using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MacOSVMPool"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Prerequisites","anchor":"Prerequisites"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple Silicon Mac (M1 or later)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"macOS 14+ on the host"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Spooktacular installed ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"brew install --cask spooktacular"},{"type":"text","text":")"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"API key from Anthropic, OpenAI, or Google"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Quick-Start-Two-OpenClaw-Instances","level":2,"text":"Quick Start: Two OpenClaw Instances"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"1. Create the first VM","anchor":"1-Create-the-first-VM"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["spook create openclaw-work --from-ipsw latest \\","    --cpu 4 --memory 8 --disk 32 \\","    --network nat \\","    --user-data .\/setup-openclaw.sh \\","    --provision disk-inject"]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"2. Clone for the second instance","anchor":"2-Clone-for-the-second-instance"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["spook clone openclaw-work openclaw-personal"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The clone takes ~50ms (APFS copy-on-write). Each VM gets a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"unique machine identifier automatically."}]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"3-Start-both","text":"3. Start both"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash","code":["spook start openclaw-work --headless","spook start openclaw-personal --headless"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Both VMs boot and run OpenClaw independently. Each listens"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on its own IP address, port 18789."}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"4-Check-status","level":3,"text":"4. Check status"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["spook list","spook ip openclaw-work","spook ip openclaw-personal"],"syntax":"bash"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"User-Data-Script-for-OpenClaw","level":2,"text":"User-Data Script for OpenClaw"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create a script that installs and configures OpenClaw automatically:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["#!\/bin\/bash","# setup-openclaw.sh — installs OpenClaw in a macOS VM","","set -euo pipefail","","# Install Homebrew (if not present)","if ! command -v brew &>\/dev\/null; then","    \/bin\/bash -c \"$(curl -fsSL https:\/\/raw.githubusercontent.com\/Homebrew\/install\/HEAD\/install.sh)\"","    eval \"$(\/opt\/homebrew\/bin\/brew shellenv)\"","fi","","# Install Node.js 24","brew install node@24","echo 'export PATH=\"\/opt\/homebrew\/opt\/node@24\/bin:$PATH\"' >> ~\/.zshrc","export PATH=\"\/opt\/homebrew\/opt\/node@24\/bin:$PATH\"","","# Install OpenClaw","npm install -g openclaw@latest","","# Run onboard with daemon installation","# (The API key should be set via environment variable or","#  injected via the shared folder)","openclaw onboard --install-daemon","","echo \"OpenClaw installed and running on port 18789\""],"syntax":"bash"},{"type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For production deployments, pass the API key via"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a shared folder or environment variable rather than"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"hardcoding it in the script."}]}],"style":"note"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Passing-API-Keys-Securely","level":3,"text":"Passing API Keys Securely"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use a shared folder to deliver configuration without"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"embedding secrets in the script:"}]},{"code":["# On the host: create a config directory","mkdir -p ~\/openclaw-configs\/work","cat > ~\/openclaw-configs\/work\/openclaw.json << 'EOF'","{","    \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250514\",","    \"anthropicApiKey\": \"sk-ant-your-key-here\"","}","EOF","","# Create VM with shared folder","spook create openclaw-work --from-ipsw latest \\","    --share ~\/openclaw-configs\/work:config:ro \\","    --user-data .\/setup-openclaw.sh"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the setup script, copy the config from the shared folder:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["# Inside setup-openclaw.sh","mkdir -p ~\/.openclaw","cp \"\/Volumes\/My Shared Files\/openclaw.json\" ~\/.openclaw\/openclaw.json","openclaw config validate"],"syntax":"bash"},{"anchor":"Kubernetes-OpenClaw-Fleet","type":"heading","text":"Kubernetes: OpenClaw Fleet","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Deploy OpenClaw instances across multiple Macs using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the Kubernetes operator:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"yaml","code":["apiVersion: spooktacular.io\/v1alpha1","kind: MacOSVMPool","metadata:","  name: openclaw-agents","  namespace: ai","spec:","  replicas: 2","  image: ghcr.io\/spooktacular\/macos:15.4","","  provisioning:","    mode: disk-inject","    userData: |","      #!\/bin\/bash","      brew install node@24","      export PATH=\"\/opt\/homebrew\/opt\/node@24\/bin:$PATH\"","      npm install -g openclaw@latest","      mkdir -p ~\/.openclaw","      # Config injected via K8s secret → shared folder","      cp \"\/Volumes\/My Shared Files\/openclaw.json\" ~\/.openclaw\/","      openclaw onboard --install-daemon","","  resources:","    cpu: 4","    memory: 8Gi","    disk: 32Gi","","  network:","    mode: nat"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each Mac in the fleet runs 2 OpenClaw VMs. Ten Macs ="},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"20 OpenClaw instances."}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Networking-Between-Instances","level":2,"text":"Networking Between Instances"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If your OpenClaw instances need to communicate (e.g.,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a coordinator agent delegating to worker agents):"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["spook create openclaw-coordinator --from-ipsw latest --network nat","spook create openclaw-worker --from-ipsw latest --network nat"],"syntax":"bash"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"NAT networking lets the VMs reach each other via their"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"DHCP-assigned IPs and the host Mac. The coordinator can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reach the worker’s gateway on port 18789. Use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/isolated","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" if you need to prevent internet"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"access entirely, communicating through shared folders"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and the VirtIO socket instead."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For internet access + inter-VM communication, use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"NAT networking — both VMs can reach each other via"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"their NAT-assigned IPs."}]},{"anchor":"Resource-Planning","type":"heading","text":"Resource Planning","level":2},{"rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Setup"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"CPU"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Memory"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Disk"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Notes"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Cloud models only"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"4 cores"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"4 GB"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"16 GB"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Minimal — OpenClaw is lightweight"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Cloud + light local models"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"4 cores"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"8 GB"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"32 GB"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Ollama with small models"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Heavy local models (Llama 3)"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"6 cores"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"16 GB"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"64 GB"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Needs unified memory"}]}]]],"type":"table","header":"row"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Since macOS VMs share the host’s unified memory via"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the Virtualization framework, the GPU (Metal) is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"available inside the VM for local model inference."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Monitoring","anchor":"Monitoring"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Check OpenClaw health in each VM:"}]},{"code":["# From the host","spook ssh openclaw-work -- \"openclaw status\"","spook ssh openclaw-personal -- \"openclaw status\"","","# Or via the gateway API","curl http:\/\/$(spook ip openclaw-work):18789\/health","curl http:\/\/$(spook ip openclaw-personal):18789\/health"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash"},{"anchor":"Snapshots","type":"heading","text":"Snapshots","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Save a working OpenClaw configuration before making changes."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The VM must be stopped to take or restore a disk-level snapshot:"}]},{"code":["spook stop openclaw-work","spook snapshot openclaw-work pre-upgrade","spook start openclaw-work --headless","# ... make changes, install new version ...","# If something breaks:","spook stop openclaw-work","spook restore openclaw-work pre-upgrade","spook start openclaw-work --headless"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash"}]}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/OpenClawGuide"},"references":{"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/Versioning":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning","role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/versioning","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Understand what version numbers mean and what to expect from each release."}],"title":"Versioning & Release Schedule"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/KubernetesGuide":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide","role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/kubernetesguide","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Manage macOS virtual machines as Kubernetes resources with custom CRDs and an operator."}],"title":"Kubernetes Integration"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/SharedFolder":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SharedFolder"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SharedFolder","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SharedFolder"}],"url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/sharedfolder","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A directory shared between the host and the virtual machine."}],"title":"SharedFolder"},"https://openclaw.ai":{"type":"link","title":"OpenClaw","identifier":"https:\/\/openclaw.ai","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","tex